    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 679.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 667, of the 11th instant, further
                    explains the grounds upon which you had made renewed demands at the Porte and
                    palace for the protection of American missionaries whose safety might appear to
                    be threatened by the events in eastern Asia Minor or elsewhere, and I have
                    pleasure in confirming the approbation heretofore given to your conduct in
                    warning the Ottoman Government that if any American—man, woman, or child—were
                    hurt, your Government would hold it responsible.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
